Unity Keyword Record Classes
In the Unity API model, there are three different classes used for Keyword Records, that allow interaction with Keywords. Each of these objects represents a Keyword Record in a different state. Below is a description of the different Keyword Record classes, as well as when each of the different classes would be used.

KeywordRecord
A KeywordRecord represents a single Keyword Record on an existing document. This record is meant for the retrieval of Keyword data, and its properties are not editable. It is accessed from the KeywordRecords property of an existing Document object.

EditableKeywordRecord
Used when archiving documents or when adding or modifying a Keyword record on an existing document. Its properties are editable, and it can be created from a KeywordRecord object, or a KeywordRecordType object.

QueryKeywordRecord
Used when querying documents. It is used to limit the results of a query, based on the Keyword values and operators stored in the QueryKeywordRecord.


