Accessing Keywords in Keyword Records
In the Unity programming model, all Keywords are stored within a Keyword Record. See the Keywords in Unity section for more general information about Keyword Records.

To find a Keyword value for an OnBase document, a developer must first retrieve to the Keyword Record that contains the Keyword. The Unity Document object contains a list of all Keyword Records stored for a given document.

Developers can use a foreach loop to iterate through all Keyword Records on a document, and another foreach loop to iterate though the Keywords in each Keyword Record. Once a Keyword object has been retrieved, developers can retrieve the properties from that Keyword, such as the Keyword Type and Keyword value.

  Note

Standalone Keyword Records return only the Keywords with values. Unlike Single-Instance and Multi-Instance Keyword Record Types, blank Keywords are not returned for Standalone Keyword Records.

