While the FindAll method used above finds all instances of Keyword Records and Keywords that meet the search criteria, the Find method returns the first instance of a Keyword Record/Keyword that meets the provided search criteria. The Find method takes one parameter which defines the search criteria. All types of search criteria listed above for the FindAll method are accepted.

  Caution

The Find method will return null if it cannot find the specified Keyword or Keyword Record. An if statement to check for null should always follow a Find in order to avoid an "Object not set to an instance of an object exception."

